.TH "drm_gem_vram_fill_create_dumb" 9 "drm_gem_vram_fill_create_dumb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gem_vram_fill_create_dumb \- Helper for implementing &struct drm_driver.dumb_create
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_gem_vram_fill_create_dumb
.BI "(struct drm_file *file "  ","
.BI "struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned long pg_align "  ","
.BI "unsigned long pitch_align "  ","
.BI "struct drm_mode_create_dumb *args "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
the DRM file
.IP "dev" 12
the DRM device
.IP "pg_align" 12
the buffer's alignment in multiples of the page size
.IP "pitch_align" 12
the scanline's alignment in powers of 2
.IP "args" 12
the arguments as provided to                            \fIstruct drm_driver\fP.dumb_create
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This helper function fills \fIstruct drm_mode_create_dumb\fP, which is used
by \fIstruct drm_driver\fP.dumb_create. Implementations of this interface
should forwards their arguments to this helper, plus the driver-specific
parameters.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or
a negative error code otherwise.
